2022 Year in Books

Michael Gillis

Every year I track the books that I read through the website Goodreads. Goodreads is a website that began in 2006, and has since been purchased by Amazon. It allows for a user to select books from their extensive catalog, adding the books to shelves like Read and Want to Read. Users can also rate books using a 5 star rating system.

At the end of every year, Goodreads compiles a Year in Books for each user. It displays different data, such as total pages read, total books read, and average rating. I found myself wishing that Goodreads would provide more in this annual summary, which lead me to realize that all of the data I needed to create my own exists within the Goodreads catlogue already.

Without further ado, here is my year in books:

Books

I read a total of 47 books this year.
The genre I read the most of this year was Mystery, with a total of 28 Mystery books read.
I read the most books in August, with a total of 7 books read that month.

Pages

I read a total of 14,697 pages this year.
I read the most pages in August reading a total of 2,114 pages that month.

Authors

The author I read most from this year was Robert B. Parker. I read a total a total of 18 of their books.
